headline: Why The Narrative Around Duke Energy (DUK) Is Shifting As Targets And Projects Evolve
summary: Analysts have fine tuned their view of Duke Energy, trimming the fair value estimate slightly from about US$135.24 to roughly US$134.71 per share, while keeping the discount rate essentially unchanged and nudging the modeled revenue growth assumption from around 5.04% to 5.06%. This reflects a careful reset of expectations as recent research balances confidence in execution and cash flow visibility with a bit more caution around how much to pay for that profile today. summary: DUK prepares to report Q4 results, with earnings expected to fall 9% year over year, even as revenue growth and power demand show resilience.

headline: Duke Energy Grants And Tax AI Efforts Frame Valuation Debate
summary: Duke Energy Foundation has awarded $500,000 in workforce development grants to North Carolina community colleges, targeting skilled trades programs. Duke Energy is participating as an early user in KPMG's new Tax AI Accelerator Program, focused on applying artificial intelligence to tax compliance. Duke Energy (NYSE:DUK), recently trading at $123.41, is pairing community investment with technology adoption in ways that can matter for long term operations. The $500,000 in workforce grants...
